    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1934-08-29T19:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1934-08-29T19:00:00-05:00" n="166"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d166">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">611.3731/1030a: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Ambassador in Cuba</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Caffery</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1934-08-29T20:00:00-04:00"
                            >August 29, 1934—8 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>184. Inter-Departmental Committee for Foreign Trade desires frequent progressive
                    reports evidencing concrete results of trade agreement in increased orders for
                    products of the United States.<note n="75" xml:id="d166fn75">For summaries of
                        reports, see Department of State, <hi rend="italic">Press Releases</hi>,
                        September 8, 1934, pp. 180–181; and November 17, 1934, pp. 297–298.</note>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Phillips</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
